
1) Start VS-22

2) Project --> Configuration --> VC++ Directories --> General
	a) Set Include Directories to \Tag23\lib\include
	b) Set Library Directories to C:\Users\...\lib\include;C:\Users\....\lib\lib-vc2019;$(LibraryPath)

3) Project --> Configuration --> Linker --> Input --> Additional Dependencies, add "glfw3.lib;opengl32.lib;" before "%(AdditionalDependencies)

If getting an error about being unable to link kernel32.lib then reinsall Visual C++ Executable.

REMEMBER TO MANUALLY ADD EVERYTHING IN src TO THE PROJECT IN VS 



